{"name":"EmailMessage","description":"Represents an email message.","summary":"In Salesforce, the object `EmailMessage` represents an email that is sent or received and is associated with other standard or custom objects like Cases, Leads, Opportunities, or Contacts. This object allows users to track and manage email communications within Salesforce.\n\nKey features of the `EmailMessage` object include:\n\n1. **Tracking and Logging**: It logs details of emails including sender, recipient, subject, body, and timestamps.\n2. **Relationships**: It links emails to relevant records, helping users see email interactions in the context of their customer relationships.\n3. **Automations**: It can be used in workflows, triggers, and other automation tools to streamline processes and improve efficiency.\n4. **Reporting**: It supports reporting and analytics, providing insights into email communications and their effectiveness.\n5. **Security**: It incorporates Salesforce’s security features to ensure email data is protected and accessible only to authorized users.\n\nOverall, the `EmailMessage` object enhances Salesforce’s CRM capabilities by integrating email communication directly into the platform.","attributes":[{"name":"Id","type":"id"},{"name":"ParentId","type":"reference"},{"name":"ActivityId","type":"reference"},{"name":"CreatedById","type":"reference"},{"name":"CreatedDate","type":"datetime"},{"name":"LastModifiedDate","type":"datetime"},{"name":"LastModifiedById","type":"reference"},{"name":"SystemModstamp","type":"datetime"},{"name":"TextBody","type":"textarea"},{"name":"HtmlBody","type":"textarea"},{"name":"Headers","type":"textarea"},{"name":"Subject","type":"string"},{"name":"FromName","type":"string"},{"name":"FromAddress","type":"email"},{"name":"ValidatedFromAddress","type":"picklist"},{"name":"ToAddress","type":"string"},{"name":"CcAddress","type":"string"},{"name":"BccAddress","type":"string"},{"name":"Incoming","type":"boolean"},{"name":"HasAttachment","ty